TITLE: Suze Orman: ‘Big mistake if you park your money forever in bonds’
SUMMARY: Personal finance expert Suze Orman believes there's a “lifetime opportunity” in the stock market.

TITLE: It may take $10 million to achieve 'financial freedom,' say 'Earn Your Leisure' hosts
SUMMARY: It's hard for most people to attain financial freedom, but trying will leave you better off, said Rashad Bilal and Troy Millings of podcast "Earn Your Leisure."

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase stock slips after bank says CEO Jamie Dimon is selling 1 million shares
SUMMARY: JPMorgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon will begin to sell 1 million shares of the bank he runs next year, the bank said.

TITLE: Elon Musk wants your 'entire financial life' on X: Report
SUMMARY: X owner Elon Musk wants to create a future in which X users can use the platform for their entire financial lives, according to a report from The Verge.

TITLE: Supermarket bank branches are closing 7 times faster than other locations
SUMMARY: PNC, Citizens Financial and U.S. Bank shut the most in-store locations recently at chains including Safeway and Stop & Shop.

TITLE: Huawei's revenue barely rose in the third quarter, despite phone and car sales growth
SUMMARY: Chinese tech giant Huawei reported revenue figures Friday that showed only a 1% increase in the third quarter from a year ago, according to CNBC calculations.

TITLE: Chinese smartphone maker Xiaomi releases a new operating system as it plans car integration
SUMMARY: Chinese smartphone and appliance maker Xiaomi announced late Thursday a new operating system — as it plans to release its own car.

TITLE: Here are 4 ways health savings accounts can be used to pay insurance premiums
SUMMARY: In rare cases, consumers can use their health savings accounts, or HSAs, to pay insurance premiums while preserving the account's tax benefits.

TITLE: Watch live: ECB President Christine Lagarde speaks after opting to hold rates
SUMMARY: European Central Bank President Christine Lagarde is giving a press conference following the bank's latest monetary policy decision.

TITLE: With China playing catchup with the U.S., these 3 charts show the top countries for fintech in 2023
SUMMARY: Using data provided by research firm Statista, CNBC analyzed the top nations overall when it comes to financial technology.

TITLE: Tesla rival Xpeng presses ahead with driver-assist rollout in China, Europe
SUMMARY: Chinese electric car company Xpeng said this week it plans to roll out driver-assist technology in Europe by the end of next year.

TITLE: Morgan Stanley says Ted Pick will succeed James Gorman as CEO on Jan. 1
SUMMARY: The announcement ends the top succession race on Wall Street. Morgan Stanley announced in May that Gorman intended to step down within a year.

TITLE: 'Incredible alpha opportunities' in the year ahead despite headwinds, says Carlyle Group CEO Harvey Schwartz
SUMMARY: Wall Street leaders speaking at the annual Riyadh event broadly expressed varying degrees of pessimism and caution for the coming year.

TITLE: Deutsche Bank shares surge 7% after net profit beats expectations
SUMMARY: Deutsche Bank reported a third-quarter net profit of 1.031 billion euros ($1.06 billion), slightly beating expectations.

TITLE: Picking health insurance can be tricky: 6 key terms to know as open enrollment starts
SUMMARY: Health plans have many moving parts such as premiums, co-insurance and deductibles that make it difficult to ascertain costs.

TITLE: China signals more support for struggling local governments
SUMMARY: The central government formalized a process for local governments to borrow for the year ahead — starting in the preceding fourth quarter, state media said.

TITLE: Coinbase shares rise 6% as Grayscale ETF ruling takes effect
SUMMARY: Coinbase is up nearly 119% year to date but remains well off its pre-crypto-winter levels.

TITLE: Jamie Dimon rips central banks for being ‘100% dead wrong’ on economic forecasts
SUMMARY: "Prepare for possibilities and probabilities, not calling one course of action, since I've never seen anyone call it," Dimon said in Saudi Arabia.

TITLE: Barclays down 6.5% after warning of fourth-quarter cost-cutting charges
SUMMARY: Barclays on Tuesday reported a net profit of £1.27 billion ($1.56 billion) for the third quarter, slightly ahead of expectations.

TITLE: Say goodbye to retirement? A 'soft saving' trend is emerging among young people
SUMMARY: Generation Z is leading the "soft saving" trend, a new financial approach that prioritizes personal growth and mental wellness over aggressive saving goals.

TITLE: Big banks are done reporting earnings. Here’s how our financial names performed against peers
SUMMARY: Some businesses performed better than others. However, none of them has been rewarded with higher stock prices — yet.

TITLE: The 'No. 1 question' Ark Invest’s Cathie Wood gets on her website
SUMMARY: The most popular question on Ark Invest’s website has nothing to do with investing in the U.S., according to the firm’s CEO Cathie Wood.

TITLE: Regional bank shares slump as lenders warn of more pain from higher interest rates
SUMMARY: Several weak quarterly earnings reports highlighting the negative effect of higher interest rates soured investor sentiment on the industry.

TITLE: Coinbase is 'confident' a U.S. bitcoin ETF will be approved after SEC's court defeat
SUMMARY: Coinbase is confident that a U.S. bitcoin exchange-traded fund will be approved by the Securities and Exchange Commission, its chief legal officer told CNBC.

TITLE: After blockbuster Microsoft deal, gaming giants are still sitting on $45 billion cash hoard
SUMMARY: Activision Blizzard, Electronic Arts and other public gaming firms hold $45.1 billion in cash and cash equivalents, according to venture capital firm Konvoy.

TITLE: Turbine troubles have sent wind energy stocks tumbling — and a slew of issues remain
SUMMARY: As the biggest players in wind energy gear up to report quarterly earnings, supply chain issues and reliability concerns are front and center.

TITLE: A $7.40 fee could ruin your next trip to Europe. Miss it and 'you won't board the plane,’ expert says
SUMMARY: Americans visiting Europe will soon need to apply and pay a fee for a travel authorization. The requirement is slated to start next year.

TITLE: Powell says inflation is still too high and lower economic growth is likely needed to bring it down
SUMMARY: Powell hinted the labor market and economic growth may need to slow to ultimately achieve the Fed's goal.

TITLE: Big banks are quietly cutting thousands of employees, and more layoffs are coming
SUMMARY: Job losses in finance could pressure the broader U.S. labor market in 2024. Faced with rising defaults on loans, lenders are poised to make deeper cuts.

TITLE: As U.S.-China tensions rumble on, fintech unicorn Airwallex pushes into Latin America with Mexico deal
SUMMARY: Global fintech giant Airwallex said it has acquired MexPago, a rival payments company based out of Mexico, for an undisclosed sum.
